edu.ucla.sspace.vector

Interface Vector<T extends Number>

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    DoubleVector, IntegerVector, SparseDoubleVector, SparseIntegerVector, SparseVector<T>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractDoubleVector, AbstractIntegerVector, AbstractVector, AmortizedSparseVector, AtomicSparseVector, AtomicVector, CompactSparseIntegerVector, CompactSparseVector, DenseDynamicMagnitudeVector, DenseIntVector, DenseVector, MaskedDoubleVectorView, MaskedSparseDoubleVectorView, ScaledDoubleVector, ScaledSparseDoubleVector, SparseHashDoubleVector, SparseHashIntegerVector, SparseHashVector, TernaryVector

    public interface Vector<T extends Number>
    An generalized interface for vectors. This interface allows implementations to implement the vector with any kind of underlying data type.
    Author:
    Keith Stevens
